#NOBOYSALLOWED

WHO WE ARE

#NOBOYSALLOWED is a collective based in San Marcos, Texas created by womxn of color for womxn of color who were tired of seeing strong and talented constantly being pushed into the background. We hope to build an inclusive community, produce unique events, and generally create a space where womxn can express their creativity in a safely and without judgement. The majority of our events have a strict no cis-boy allowed policy for that very reason. If you’re interested in collaborating on a project, being featured on our website, or sponsoring a #NOBOYSALLOWED event, email us at noboysallowedsmtx@gmail.com 

What is the background (right) used throughout your website?                                                                                                                       The #NOBOYSALLOWED collage was made in October 2018 by the members of the collective as the accumulation of their creativity. It’s meant to represent a womanist utopia where womxn of different backgounds and identities live in the clouds. It’s currently used as the background for the photobooth at all of our official events, so make sure to swing by and take a photo!
